            <title>[JDK-8323086] Shenandoah: Heap could be corrupted by oom during evacuation</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8323086</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>When the load reference barrier is unable to evacuate an object, it initiates a degenerated cycle, and allows the from-space reference past the barrier. The degenerated cycle is meant to patch up these references, but if the reference is written above the update-watermark, it will be missed.</description>
